# .cursorrules for go-web (AutoImport GH Landing Page)

## Project
Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript strict, CSS Modules.
Marketing landing page for AutoImport GH - Ghana vehicle import platform.

## Architecture
src/
  app/            Next.js App Router - layout.tsx, page.tsx, globals.css
  components/
    layout/       Nav, Footer
    sections/     One file per page section
    ui/           Button, Badge, SectionLabel primitives
  lib/
    content.ts    ALL copy, stats, links - single source of truth
    constants.ts  Brand colors, breakpoints

## Rules
- ALL text lives in lib/content.ts - never hardcoded in components
- CSS Modules only - no Tailwind, no inline styles except dynamic values
- CSS custom properties from globals.css - no hardcoded color values in modules
- DM Sans + Syne via next/font/google
- Every component is a named export
- Props interfaces defined above components
- Section components take no props - read from content.ts
- 'use client' only when interactivity is required
- No any, no as any
- Semantic HTML - section, nav, footer, h1, h2, p
- Mobile-first media queries - min-width breakpoints
- next/image for all images with width + height
# .cursorrules for go-web (AutoImport GH Landing Page)

## Project
Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript (strict), CSS Modules.
No Tailwind. No class-variance-authority. No shadcn.
Marketing landing page for AutoImport GH — a Ghana vehicle import platform.

## Architecture — Feature-Sliced Design (marketing variant)
```
src/
  app/                    Next.js App Router
    layout.tsx            Root layout — fonts, metadata, globals
    page.tsx              Composes section components top to bottom
    globals.css           CSS custom properties, reset, base typography
  components/
    layout/               Nav, Footer
    sections/             One file per page section
    ui/                   Reusable primitives — Button, Badge, SectionLabel
  lib/
    content.ts            ALL copy, stats, links — single source of truth
    constants.ts          Brand colors, breakpoints, animation values
  public/
    images/               Placeholder + real images
```

## Strict Rules

### Content
- ALL text content (headings, body copy, labels, stats) lives in lib/content.ts
- NO hardcoded strings in components — always import from content.ts
- Placeholders are marked with a PLACEHOLDER comment in content.ts

### Styling
- CSS Modules only — one .module.css per component file
- CSS custom properties defined in globals.css, used everywhere
- DM Sans + Syne fonts — loaded via next/font/google
- Brand primary: #378ADD, dark: #1A1A18 — always use CSS variables
- Mobile-first media queries — min-width breakpoints
- NO inline styles except for dynamic values (e.g. animation progress)

### Components
- Every component is a named export, not default export
- Props interfaces defined above the component with explicit types
- No prop drilling beyond 2 levels — use content.ts for static data
- Section components receive no props — they read from content.ts directly
- UI primitives (Button, Badge) receive props

### TypeScript
- strict mode — no any, no as any
- All content.ts exports are typed with interfaces
- No non-null assertions unless absolutely necessary

### Performance
- Images use next/image with explicit width/height
- Fonts loaded with next/font/google (subset: latin)
- Sections use IntersectionObserver for scroll animations
- No client components unless interactivity is required
- Mark client components with 'use client' only when needed

### SEO
- Metadata exported from app/layout.tsx
- Semantic HTML — section, nav, footer, h1, h2, p
- Alt text on all images (from content.ts)
- Open Graph tags in layout metadata

### No
- No useState/useEffect for static content
- No external UI libraries
- No Tailwind
- No class-based components
- No default exports on components
- No hardcoded colors in CSS Modules (use var(--color-*))